  <h1>👨‍💻 Getting Started in Cybersecurity</h1>
  <p>
    Welcome to your cybersecurity journey! Whether you're completely new or have a little experience, this page will help you understand where to begin, what to learn, and how to build your skills effectively.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>🔐 What is Cybersecurity?</h2>
  <p>
    Cybersecurity is the practice of defending systems, networks, and programs from digital attacks. It covers a wide range of roles—from protecting sensitive data to performing ethical hacking to find and fix vulnerabilities before attackers do.
  </p>

  <blockquote style="font-style: italic; color: #58a6ff;">
    “Hacking is not about breaking into systems. It's about knowing them better than anyone else.” — Unknown
  </blockquote>

  <h2>🧭 Cybersecurity Career Paths</h2>
  <ul class="resource-list">
    <li>🛡️ <strong>Blue Team</strong> – Defenders (SOC Analyst, Threat Hunter, Incident Responder)</li>
    <li>⚔️ <strong>Red Team</strong> – Ethical Hackers (Pentester, Bug Bounty Hunter, Red Team Ops)</li>
    <li>🛠️ <strong>Engineering</strong> – Secure Code, DevSecOps, Security Automation</li>
    <li>📋 <strong>Governance</strong> – Risk Analyst, Compliance, Policy Creation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>💡 Fundamental Concepts</h2>
  <ul class="resource-list">
    <li><strong>Confidentiality</strong> – Preventing unauthorized access to data</li>
    <li><strong>Integrity</strong> – Ensuring data isn’t tampered with</li>
    <li><strong>Availability</strong> – Making sure services are reliable & accessible</li>
    <li><strong>Authentication vs Authorization</strong> – Know the difference!</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🧰 Skills to Focus On (2025)</h2>
  <ul class="resource-list">
    <li>🔧 Basic Linux (Kali, Ubuntu), Command Line tools</li>
    <li>🌐 Web Basics (HTTP, Cookies, Sessions, JS, Forms)</li>
    <li>📡 Networking (TCP/IP, DNS, VPNs, Firewalls)</li>
    <li>🔍 Vulnerabilities: XSS, SQLi, IDOR, CSRF, SSRF</li>
    <li>🧪 Bug bounty mindset & recon methods</li>
    <li>📦 Tools: Burp Suite, Nmap, FFUF, Amass, Subfinder</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🧑‍🏫 How to Learn Effectively</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>✅ Learn the basics from free platforms</li>
    <li>🎯 Set goals (e.g. Hack one TryHackMe room/week)</li>
    <li>🔁 Practice regularly (don’t skip hands-on)</li>
    <li>📖 Read real bug bounty writeups & CTF walkthroughs</li>
    <li>👥 Join communities (Reddit, Discord, Twitter/X)</li>
  </ol>

